## Architecture -- The Druckenmiller Model
High conviction, concentrated bets. Few trades. Large sizes when right. Fast exits when wrong. Stay in cash most of the time.

NOT Renaissance (thousands of tiny bets). NOT conservative institutional (monthly limits, cash reserves). Druckenmiller: when the signal is right, go big. When wrong, exit fast.

## Five Non-Negotiable Rules (and nothing else)
1. Max 2 orders per cycle -- Knight Capital prevention
2. Order fill verification -- confirm fill before placing stop loss
3. Daily 3% loss limit -- one circuit breaker only
4. Friday short close rule -- all shorts closed by 3:30 PM ET Fridays, no new shorts after 2 PM ET Fridays
5. Stop loss atomic with entry -- if stop fails, position closes immediately

## Conviction Sizing
- 3 of 5 Misfits vote TRADE plus Jane Street approves: 5% of portfolio
- 4 of 5: 8% of portfolio
- 5 of 5: 10% of portfolio
- Omniscient Rotation high conviction: 15% of portfolio
- VIX above 35: all sizes cut 50%
