## Known Risks (managed not eliminated)
- Leveraged ETF gap risk -- TQQQ and SOXL can gap 20 to 30% in a single day. 5% stop loss does not fully protect against gap through. Accepted risk, managed by VIX circuit breaker.
- Scorecard resets on Railway restart -- training loop data is in-memory only. Persists within a session but resets on redeploy. Future build: persist to external store.
- yfinance rate limiting -- possible stale data on heavy download cycles. Accepted risk, monitored in logs.
- Paper vs live slippage -- paper trading assumes perfect fills. Live trading will have slippage especially in leveraged ETFs. Account for this before scaling position sizes.

